  "prompt": "What should I do if my best friend's friend likes me but I like my best friend?",
  "response": "Navigating feelings in friendships can be challenging, especially when multiple emotions and relationships are involved. Here's a thoughtful approach to your situation:\n\n1. **Acknowledge Your Feelings:**\n   - **Self-Reflection:** Take some time to understand your feelings for both your best friend and the friend who likes you. Consider what you value most in your relationships and what you're genuinely seeking.\n\n2. **Assess the Situation:**\n   - **Friendship Dynamics:** Think about how pursuing a romantic relationship with either person might affect your existing friendships. Prioritize the importance of your current relationships and the potential consequences of any changes.\n   - **Their Feelings:** Consider how your best friend might feel if they knew about their friend\u2019s interest in you and your feelings toward your best friend.\n\n3. **Communicate Openly and Honestly:**\n   - **With Your Best Friend:** If you feel comfortable, consider sharing your feelings with your best friend. Honesty can strengthen your bond, but be prepared for various reactions and respect their feelings as well.\n   - **With Their Friend:** It might be considerate to address the friend who likes you. Gently letting them know where you stand can prevent misunderstandings and preserve mutual respect.\n\n4. **Set Boundaries if Needed:**\n   - **Managing Interactions:** Depending on how conversations unfold, you might need to set clear boundaries to ensure that all parties feel respected and that your best friendship remains strong.\n   \n5. **Seek Support:**\n   - **Trusted Individuals:** Talk to another trusted friend or a counselor about your feelings. They can offer objective perspectives and support as you navigate the situation.\n\n6. **Prioritize Respect and Empathy:**\n   - **Understand Everyone\u2019s Feelings:** Recognize that all individuals involved have emotions and perspectives. Strive to handle the situation with kindness and understanding to maintain harmony.\n\n7. **Take Your Time:**\n   - **Don\u2019t Rush Decisions:** Give yourself the space to make thoughtful decisions rather than reacting impulsively. This can lead to better outcomes for all relationships involved.\n\n8. **Consider the Long-Term:**\n   - **Future Implications:** Think about how different actions might impact your relationships in the long run. Prioritizing the health and longevity of your friendships is often more fulfilling than pursuing short-term interests.\n\n**Example Steps You Might Take:**\n- Spend some quiet time journaling your feelings to gain clarity.\n- Have a one-on-one conversation with your best friend about your feelings, being honest yet sensitive.\n- Speak privately with the friend who likes you to acknowledge their feelings and express yours clearly.\n\nRemember, there's no one-size-fits-all solution, and it's essential to handle the situation with care to preserve the trust and respect in your friendships. Prioritizing open communication and empathy will help navigate this delicate scenario.",
